CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "City's Evidence - As reasons for the condemnation of the Winfield St. tenement houses of Alfred E. Davis, city officials cited such defects as (arrows) a deteriorating foundation with mortar falling out, and rotting porches. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Winfield tenement houses with clapboard siding, wooden stairs, litter, and crumbling block foundation, Winfield Street, East Liberty
